snippet: Representative Adam Kinzinger, Republican of Illinois, said that if House Republicans can’t rally behind the proposal their leadership rolled out Tuesday morning, they will likely be forced to accept the plan taking shape in the Senate.
abstract: Representative Adam Kinzinger, Republican of Illinois, said that if House Republicans can’t rally behind the proposal their leadership rolled out Tuesday morning, they will likely be forced to accept the plan taking shape in the Senate.

headline.main: Republican Says House May Be Forced into Senate Plan
